  "abstract": "The Semi-Arid Tropics of the world are\r\ncharacterised by shQrt wet period and long\r\ndry periods. The evapotranspiration\r\ndemand of the climate far exceeds the precipitation\r\nfor most part of the year.\r\nAccording to Troll (1966), the areas characterised\r\nby 2At wet months (P> ET) and\r\n10 to 7t dry months are classified as dry\r\nsemi-arid tropics whereas 4-7 wet months\r\nand 8-5 dry months are considered humid\r\nsemi-arid tropics...",
